title: Bug 6322: All types dialog displays obfuscated classes
description: When accessing the 'All types' dialog in JDK 1.4, obfuscated classes (e.g., 'a', 'a1', 'b', 'c', 'd', etc.) are shown.
OB: The 'All types' dialog in JDK 1.4 displays obfuscated classes alongside regular classes.
EB: The 'All types' dialog should only display regular classes without showing obfuscated ones.
SR:
Steps to reproduce:
1. Access the 'All types' dialog in JDK 1.4.
2. Observe the inclusion of obfuscated classes such as 'a', 'a1', 'b', 'c', 'd', etc.
Expected behavior: Obfuscated classes should not be listed within the 'All types' dialog.
